translations.en: They walk to the house.
We open the house door.
He bought a new house.
My son goes to school.
She walks to school every day.
translations.lt: Ji kiekvieną dieną eina į mokyklą.

translations.en: My friend works at the hospital.
She went to the hospital yesterday.
I buy bread at the store.
She found a toy in the store.
We close the store at night.
They walked to the store yesterday.
We eat at the restaurant today.
My friend works at a restaurant.
I am walking to the bank today.
My friend works at the bank.
She walks to the library today.
We are visiting the museum today.
She walks to the museum.
They saw paintings at the museum.
My friend works at the museum.
The fire station is near the school.
My friend works at the fire station.
They drove past the fire station.
We ate warm bread with butter.
translations.lt: Mes valgėme šiltą duoną su sviestu.

translations.en: She buys meat at the market.
They eat meat for dinner.
My friend does not like meat.
She adds sugar to her tea.
We bought sugar at the store.
They want sugar in their coffee.
She puts salt on the meat.
I need salt for the soup.
They bought salt at the store.
My friend tastes salt on bread.
translations.lt: Mano draugas ragauja druską ant duonos.

translations.en: They buy potatoes at the market.
He bought three apples yesterday.
My friend gave me an apple.
I eat a banana every morning.
We bought tomatoes at the market.
He puts a tomato in the salad.
She eats rice every day.
My friend wants more rice.
They bought tomato soup at lunch.
My friend ate soup with bread.
translations.lt: Mano draugas suvalgė sriubą su duona.

translations.en: I buy food at the market.
They have food in their bags.
Do you like this food?
He is wearing a clean shirt today.
She bought a blue shirt.
They found a dirty shirt.
I bought new pants yesterday.
Do they have clean pants?
She is wearing a red dress today.
My friend bought a blue dress.
They see the dress in the store.
He wears a warm jacket today.
She bought a new jacket yesterday.
My shoe is by the door.
They wear the same shoes.
She lost one blue sock.
He put on clean socks.
She is wearing a black hat today.
He took off his hat.
Do you want my warm hat?
My friend bought warm gloves.
She is wearing a blue sweater today.
My friend bought a sweater yesterday.
They put the sweater on the chair.
She bought new underwear yesterday.
We ate pizza after school.
The dog will not eat.
I drink water after running.
She drank coffee this morning.
He rides his bicycle to school.
translations.lt: Jis važiuoja savo dviračiu į mokyklą.

translations.en: She bought a new bicycle yesterday.
They want a red bicycle.
I took a taxi home.
She waits for a taxi.
We saw a yellow taxi.
They called a taxi yesterday.
The truck is loud today.
My friend bought a new truck.
She puts a fork beside her plate.
translations.lt: Ji padeda šakutę prie savo lėkštės.

translations.en: I lost my fork at lunch.
translations.lt: Aš praradau savo šakutę per pietus.

translations.en: They bought new forks for dinner.
She drinks tea from a cup.
She put the plate on the table.
She reads a new book.
I found the book yesterday.
My friend gave me a book.
They put the book on the table.
My friend lost his cell phone.
translations.lt: Mano draugas prarado savo mobilųjį telefoną.

translations.en: He found a cell phone yesterday.
She carries a bag to school.
He bought a new bag today.
She opened her wallet and smiled.
translations.lt: Ji atidarė savo piniginę ir nusišypsojo.

translations.en: We lost our wallet at the market.
My friend lost his eyeglasses.
She opens the bottle now.
He puts the bottle on the table.
We found an empty bottle.
They drink from the bottle.
She looks in the mirror now.
I put the mirror on the wall.
I left a towel on the chair.
My dog sleeps on the bed.
She walked the dog yesterday.
Do you see the dog?
My friend has a black cat.
She saw a cat by the door.
A bird sits on the fence.
